{
  "texts": [
    "They extract edge and planar features from each point cloud and transform these features into a common reference frame aligned with the most recent acquisition time from all LiDARs.",
    "While these approaches successfully estimate robot trajectories, they also introduce additional challenges.",
    "IMU propagation, which is inherently discrete due to its frequency, requires additional linear interpolation, potentially leading to additional errors.",
    "Moreover, as time discrepancies become more pronounced, the duration required to accumulate the point clouds increases, which further intensifies the dependence on IMU for state propagation.",
    "However, the accuracy of the IMU propagation deteriorates over extended periods due to noise, which can adversely impact the odometry.In addressing the challenge of discrete IMU propagation, MA-LIO [64] adopts B-spline interpolation [131] as an alternative for linear interpolation, effectively compensating for temporal discrepancies."
  ]
}